{{ASCII}}
In ''[[NetHack]]'', the letter '''B''' serves the following purposes:

* {{white|b}} represents a [[blob]]:
** {{monsymlink|acid blob}}
** {{monsymlink|quivering blob}}
** {{monsymlink|gelatinous cube}}

* {{white|B}} represents a [[bat or bird]]:
** {{monsymlink|bat}}
** {{monsymlink|giant bat}}
** {{monsymlink|raven}}
** {{monsymlink|vampire bat}}

* It is also used as a [[direction]] key if [[numpad]] movement is off:
** Press {{kbd|b}} to move south-west.
** Press {{kbd|shift|b}} to move far south-west.

==Historical uses==
In hack121, a port of [[Jay Fenlason's Hack]], bats and vampire bats used the {{white|b}} glyph, while giant bears used the {{white|B}} glyph. In PDP-11 Hack and [[Hack 1.0]], the {{white|B}} glyph is given to bats, and the {{white|b}} glyph is given to the [[giant beetle]]. Both monsters retain their glyph for their appearance in [[Hack 1.0]].

The bat still uses {{white|B}} as its current glyph, while the giant beetle retains its {{white|b}} glyph up to [[NetHack 2.3e]]. In [[NetHack 3.0.0]], giant beetles are moved to {{white|a}} with other [[insect]]s, and the [[blob]] [[monster class]] is created and given the {{white|b}} glyph; the acid blob, quivering blob and gelatinous cube are moved to the blob monster class.

